        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:28PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Enfield, or 7 miles west of Ithaca, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cayuga Heights, Enfield, Northeast Ithaca, Allan H. Treman State
Marine Park, Buttermilk Falls State Park, Ithaca, Taughannock Falls,
West Dryden, Freeville, and Ithaca Tompkins Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
